"I'm not mapping much these days, but I came across this town in xenogears and it inspired me. Also the abstract map pack (http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/23695) was coming up for the joe.to community, so I figured this would be the perfect occasion.

The map is called de_shevat_ka, named after the same town in xenogears. They're even a couple songs from the game in the map.

And originally I didn't set out to make a KA map, but this is the way it turned out. And it's not all that bad as there are two bomb sites that keep the action from just being runing around knifing.

Anywho, here are some shots."

After many requests, here it is, shevat with buyzones.
I tried putting as much cover as I could to prevent too much sniper spam, but I still see that being a problem.

Hopefully it doesn't play too unbalanced, and is still fun.


Don't forget to check out the original, de_shevat_ka, and the shotgun version, de_shevat_m3.

<b>Die0's Notes:

A medium to large de map of an old facility with 2 bombsites created by Die0. The map features a small outside area (T spawn) with a spectacular view and a large underground facility where most of the action takes place. The map's plan is very distinctive. With numerous hallways, rooms, intersections, and an accessible vent system it is pretty easy to get lost. However the planning of the map ensures that all the passages intersect often and that it is easy to find bombsites as well as to defend them. The zip includes a manually tuned nav file. With it bots never get stuck and make good opponents on this map.

This is my first Counter-Strike: Source map so go easy on me. The original plan for this map was huge and I'm still deciding on whether or not it's finished. The map is big enough and you can have a great  8 player match.

A terrorist organisation has threatened to bomb a network of sewers if their demands are not met.  As negotiations spiral out of control, the counter terrorists are given the green light to go in and bring an end to the chaos through any means necessary.  The terrorists have identified two weak points in the structure, and hope to release disease and waste into the atmosphere through the bombings.

Go go go!



- Starving Hobo

I'd like to pay a special thanks to Chizbone, who made the nav file!  If it wasn't for him, the nav would be a crappy automatically generated one, thanks : )

de_severance_beta

A bomb defuse map with 64 player spawns, optimized fps and radar file.
There is a small outside area (Bombspot A), a whineceller, many corridors and a nuclear laboratory (bomspot B).

This is the beta version so if you got ideas how to improve stuff please post :)

Enjoy playing it! :)

After 6 beta-versions here the final de_severance.
This map takes place in a setting of  corridors, office rooms, a whinecellar, a nuclear lab, an outside village area, apartments and tunnels.
The counter-terrorists start in a garage with generators, while the terrorists start in a nice botanical hall. Designated bomb areas are; outside area and nuclear lab at water reservoir - A and B respectively.
The map isn´t that huge, so with 64 players it gets a lil cramped, though still playable :)

There are:
- 64 Player-spawns
- 2 Bombspots
- radar map in bsp
- soundscapes
- rendered with lightmapscale 4

render-time: 2 min 47 sec

Optimized, balanced and tested with and for 64 Players on the Sachsenkneipe servers.

Special thanks to www.sachsenkneipe.de for testing and improving it!
Sachsenkneipe XL - 64 Slots: 193.192.58.170:27015

Enjoy playing it :)

Seven story building. 
Currently there is one bomb site on which is located on the roof.
There are a couple ways to get to the roof for both teams.
All ladders work (even on the dumpster and the portable one) and all doors work. 


Notes:
-  This is obviously my first map. Not just my first CS:S map, but my first map ever.
-  Bots don't do very well inside the building, I haven't worked on their paths at all.
-  This beta is mostly for layout and I welcome all useful comments and suggestions.


Things I am planning on changing:
-  The C4 explosion kills you just about everywhere
-  Lighting and details (different textures, objects, etc...)
-  Change bounding box into a more realistic environment
-  Change most wooden crates into other objects (cars, trees, etc...)
-  Make a small building out of the two-walled sector near T spawn
-  Detail the insides of the rooms
-  Possibly spread out the spawns so they are farther from the objective building
-  Maybe a basement with a bombsite and a couple different entrances

FYI, this map won't actually crash your server. I just thought the name would be kinda funny to have.

This map consists of a total of 4 texures. Green, black, white and a ladder texture. The green, black, and white textures are all custom made textures but the ladder texture is one provided by sourceSDK. 

This map is meant to confuse, annoy, and mess with people's minds. Because of the repetitive colors of black and white, it can really throw you off track where you are keeping a good sense of direction is near impossible. And on top of that I inluded 2 death pits and a bomb site. The death pits can be acessed by climbing a ladder into them or simply jumping into them. Once you are in it you will be teleported extremely high above the map and fall to your death. It is really very funny watching people do this because they hit so hard they often times bounce off the ground. Also with the addition of the bomb site, if you go into the death pit at the right time right as the bomb is about to explode, you'll be throw throughout the map.  but overall, the gameplay is good in this map.

Woo proudly presents.... De_secureroom v6!
This map features:
-Very tactical gameplay
-A very large underground facility, complete with weapons room, ventilation shafts, large secureable doors and the ability to call a missile strike!
-Balanced gameplay
-Cool lift and plenty of traps
-Loads of security cameras
-And much more!

The CT's start at the bottom of the complex, in two linked rooms. The enterances to these rooms are via large metal doors, which can be locked from the inside. The only other way is through the ventilation...
The T's start outside, and have to get in, and to the CT spawn to plant the bomb. They can get there by going down the lift, throuhg the ventilation shafts, or if your feeling lucky, down a large air intake tunnel, complete with deadly spinning fan!

Check out some more of my maps on our server!

Welcome to Sector21!

Terrorist's- The scientists within the top secret lab, Sector21, are on the brink of a new breakthrough of chemcial weapons.  

1.  Target B- is a holding room where the chemicals are being stored and studied.  Destory the holding pool of chemicals.

2.  Target A- The warehouse/storage facility for the scientists.  It holds precious machinery/supplies to keep the lab active. 

Counter-Terrorists-  You've been called in on a special mission to protect Sector21 at all costs.  It's purpse is of excessive importance to the United States Military and must sustain its active procedures.  Protect the warehouse and the holding facilities at all costs.  Destroy any and all resistance.
